Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Feuding factions over the leadership of the International Pentecost Holiness Church have agreed to resolve their differences and stop the violence. The agreement follows a meeting with the CRL Rights Commission on Friday. READ:Â CRL Rights Commission condemns deadly church attack Two weeks ago, congregants were held hostage, and at least 5 people died in the violence at the Zuurbekom Church. Over 40 people, including a police officer, soldier, and a metro police officer have been arrested. The church has more than three million congregants in Southern Africa. Courtesy #DStv403